name: Amber Alert
summary: Several AMBER Alerts involving missing children were reported and subsequently cancelled in different parts of the United States. In Arkansas, an AMBER Alert for an 11-month-old infant from Little Rock was deactivated after the child was found safe. In Texas, two boys missing after an AMBER Alert out of Tyler were also located safely. A kidnapping investigation in Tulare County, California, resulted in the arrest of two suspects and the recovery of the children involved. An Amber Alert for a 15-month-old child in West Virginia was cancelled once the child was found safe. In Houston, Texas, an AMBER Alert for a 7-year-old girl who was abducted after a CPS investigation was inactivated after the girl was found alive. An Amber Alert in Florida also concluded successfully with the child being recovered.

summary: Colorado Buffaloes star Travis Hunter made history by winning the 2024 Heisman Trophy. Hunter also won the AP Player of the Year award and the Biletnikoff Award for best wide receiver. His father witnessed him clinch the Heisman Trophy from his mother's home in Boynton Beach, making it a special moment for the family. Hunter's remarkable achievement marks the closest Heisman race since 2009.
